THE gaping pothole on the provincial R55 road in Laudium, Tshwane, will burn a huge hole in the Gauteng government’s pockets.

 Large parts of the road caved in at the weekend. 

 Premier David Makhura said yesterday the bill to fix the tarred road will come in at a whopping R46 million.
